      <body>
         <entry xml:id="egdiqos-dlgenr"
                xml:lang="en"
                type="mainEntry"
                prev="#agbastos-dlgenr"
                next="#augustalios-dlgenr"
                source="Genesis Rabbah">
            <form type="lemma" opt="false">
               <orth type="lemma" xml:lang="jpa" opt="false" select="true">אגדיקוס</orth>
               <orth type="transliteration" xml:lang="fjb" opt="false">ʾgdyqws</orth>
               <pron notation="rabbinic" opt="false">egdiqos</pron>
               <gramGrp opt="false">
                  <gram type="pos" opt="false">noun</gram>
                  <gram type="gen" opt="false">m</gram>
               </gramGrp>
               <form type="variant" source="Vat2" opt="false">
                  <orth type="variant" xml:lang="jpa" opt="false">אגריקוס</orth>
               </form>
               <form type="variant" source="Ox1" opt="false">
                  <orth type="variant" xml:lang="jpa" opt="false">אגריקוס</orth>
               </form>
               <form type="variant" source="Ox2" opt="false">
                  <orth type="variant" xml:lang="jpa" opt="false">אגריקוס</orth>
               </form>
               <form type="variant" source="V" opt="false">
                  <orth type="variant" xml:lang="jpa" opt="false">אנדיקוס</orth>
               </form>
            </form>
            <sense xml:id="egdiqos-dlgenr-1" opt="false">
               <usg type="domain" opt="false">administration/law</usg>
               <usg type="socioCultural" norm="borrowing" opt="false">cultural borrowing</usg>
               <usg type="normativity" opt="false">standard</usg>
               <usg type="meaningType" opt="false">lit.</usg>
               <usg type="geographic" opt="false">Coptic</usg>
               <cit type="translation" xml:lang="en" subtype="sense">
                  <quote>governor, prefect, public prosecutor</quote>
               </cit>
               <cit type="translationEquivalent" xml:lang="grc">
                  <usg opt="false">
                     <lang opt="false">Post-Classical Greek</lang>
                  </usg>
                  <quote xml:lang="grc">ἔκδικος</quote>
               </cit>
               <cit type="example" xml:lang="jpa">
                  <quote>אגדיקוס במדינה ממונה על ביה שלה</quote>
                  <bibl default="false" status="draft">
                     <ref type="witness">10,12</ref>
                     <ref type="witness">I 108:4</ref>
                  </bibl>
                  <ref type="entry" xml:lang="jpa" target="biyyah.html">ביה</ref>
                  <cit type="translation" xml:lang="en">
                     <quote>the prosecutor in his province is appointed over its dominion</quote>
                  </cit>
               </cit>
            </sense>
            <etym type="borrowing" opt="false">
               <lbl opt="false">source language</lbl>
               <lang opt="false">Post-Classical Greek</lang>
               <cit type="etymon" xml:lang="grc">
                  <xr type="related" opt="false">
                     <lbl opt="false">Cf. LSJ</lbl>
                     <ref target="http://www.perseus.tufts.edu/hopper/morph?l=e%29%2Fkdi%5Ek-os&amp;la=greek&amp;can=e%29%2Fkdi%5Ek-os0"
                          type="entry">ἔκδικος, II., 3</ref>
                  </xr>
               </cit>
            </etym>
            <note anchored="true">
               Generally: public representative of Roman citizen in foreign land 
               (<bibl type="modern" default="false" status="draft">Sokoloff SL, 6</bibl>). According to Sperber <term xml:lang="jpa">אגדיקוס שבמדינה</term>
               in GenR is a translation of lat. defensor civitatis. Sperber suggests 
               that <term xml:lang="jpa">אגריקוס</term> (in 
      <bibl type="ancient" default="false" status="draft">GenR Ox 1</bibl> and
      <bibl type="ancient" default="false" status="draft">2</bibl>) might be
               influenced by Gr. <term xml:lang="grc">ἄγροικος</term>, countrydweller.
   </note>
            <ref type="bibliography">
               <bibl default="false" status="draft">
                  <title>Sperber</title>
                  <citedRange>96</citedRange>
               </bibl>
            </ref>
         </entry>
